objects.name: goofy guineapig
objects.description: Goofy Guineapig is a persistent Windows backdoor distributed as a trojanised, UPX-packed NSIS Firefox installer. After unpacking, it masquerades as a Google update component, maintaining persistence as a Windows service. The malware supports loading additional plugins, multiple communication methods (HTTP, HTTPS, and KCP/UDP), and uses embedded configuration data for C2 over HTTPS. It implements extensive defense evasion such as process hollowing, file obfuscation, anti-debug checks, anti-sandbox detection, and file deletion. System information is collected and exfiltrated, and tasking supports dynamic plugin operation.

objects.name: GoofyGuineapig_sessionstate
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule GoofyGuineapig_sessionstate
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Detects session state stack string setup in Goofy
Guineapig."
        date = "2022-12-13"
        hash1 = "11b82826ec01aeec44e5e2504935b6aaccf51cac"

    strings:
        $1 = {66 C7 45 E8 44 69 66 C7 45 F2 65 64 C6 45 F1 74 66 C7 45 EB
63 6F C6 45 F4 00 C6 45 EA 73 C7 45 ED 6E 6E 65 63}
        $2 = {66 C7 45 ED 65 00 C7 45 E8 41 63 74 69 C6 45 EC 76 EB 2A}

    condition:
        uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
        uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
        all of them
}
